Brush the pork fillet with char siu sauce. Heat the oil in same large pan and cook the pork, turning occasionally, until browned all over and just cooked through. Transfer to a warm plate, cover and leave to rest for 5 mins.
Meanwhile, place noodles in a large heatproof bowl. Cover with boiling water and leave to stand for 2 mins. Drain well.
To make the dressing, combine all the ingredients in a screw-top jar and shake well.
Slice the pork thinly and mix gently with the noodles, cabbage, snap peas, carrots, chives and dressing. Sprinkle with sesame seeds and serve.

title: cherry and raisin loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line an 8x5 inch loaf pan with parchment paper. Grease paper.

Cream butter, lemon zest and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well between additions. Add fruit. Combine self-rising flour and all-purpose flour. Combine sour cream and lemon juice. Add flour and sour cream mixture alternately to batter. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 1 hour 15 mins. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: falafel
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add fava beans and bring back to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins. Drain.

In a food processor, combine fava beans, chickpeas, parsley, cumin, coriander, salt, baking soda, onion, flour and egg. Process until almost smooth. Shape level tablespoons of mixture into patties and arrange on a baking tray. Cover and chill for 30 mins.
Heat vegetable oil in a wok. Working in batches, deep-fry falafels until browned. Drain on paper towels.

title: salmon blini with egg
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve the baking soda in 1 tbsp milk. Sift flour into a large bowl and make a well in the center.

Using a fork, lightly whisk egg yolk and remaining milk into the soda mixture. Gradually add to flour, whisking until smooth. Mix in salmon, stirring until evenly combined. In a small bowl, whisk egg white until soft peaks form and gently fold through salmon mixture.

Spray a large non-stick frying pan with oil and heat on medium. Drop ladlefuls of the mixture in the pan and flatten. Cook for 4-5 mins on one side, until bubbles appear. Turn over and cook for 1-2 mins. Transfer to a wire rack while you cook the remaining blini.
Spread blini with cream cheese. Top with pepper, egg and chives to serve.

title: hazelnut loaf cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and line an 8 x 5-inch loaf pan with parchment paper, extending the paper over long sides for handles.

Beat the butter, sugar and vanilla extract in a large bowl with an electric mixer until very pale and creamy. Gradually beat in the eggs one at a time. Fold in the combined flour and baking powder. Fold in 3/4 cup of the chopped hazelnuts. Spoon into the prepared pan, smoothing the top.

Bake for 1-1 1/4 hrs or until risen, golden and a toothpick inserted into the cake comes out clean. Cover loosely with foil after 45 mins if the cake starts to over-brown. Cool in pan 10 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

Slice the cake horizontally into 3 layers. Sandwich back together with the cherry jam. Mix the powdered sugar and lemon juice in a bowl to make a smooth thick icing. Drizzle over the top of the cake then sprinkle with the remaining hazelnuts. Let stand until the icing has set.

title: tabbouleh with grilled eggplant
directions: Place the bulgur in a small bowl, top with the tomatoes and their juice, cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, until bulgur is soft.
Preheat a grill or grill pan over high heat. Brush eggplant wedges with half the oil and cook, turning, for 10 mins, or until browned and tender.
Meanwhile, combine the tomato mixture with the parsley, mint, onion, lemon juice and remaining oil. Season to taste. Serve with eggplant wedges.

title: seafood and vegetable tempura
directions: Sift the flour into a large bowl. Season to taste. Gradually whisk in combined 1 cup iced water and egg yolks until combined. (The batter will be lumpy.)

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a wok or a deep saucepan on high heat. (Oil is ready when a cube of bread crisps quickly without absorbing oil). Dust the shrimp and vegetables in additional flour, shaking off any excess. Dip in the batter, draining off excess.
Deep-fry a few shrimp and vegetables at a time, turning, for about 2-3 mins, or until golden. Drain on paper towels. Serve mixed tempura with teriyaki sauce.

title: crab with spicy tomato sauce
directions: In a small food processor, combine onion, chilli and garlic. Pulse to form a paste. Heat oil in a large wok on medium. Cook paste 8-10 mins, stirring often, until starting to caramelize. Stir in combined sauces, sugar and vinegar. Cook 2-3 mins, to reduce slightly. Add crab and toss well. Stir-fry 8-10 mins, until shell turns red and meat is opaque. Add egg and toss with crab until just set. Serve with cilantro leaves and lime wedges.

title: chocolate pavlovas with strawberries
directions: Preheat oven to 250°F. Grease a baking sheet. Mark six 3-inch circles on a large sheet of parchment and place paper on baking sheet, marked-side down.

Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in small bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form. Gradually add 1 cup plus 2 tbsp sugar, beating until dissolved between additions. Fold in sifted cocoa and cornstarch, then vinegar.
Divide mixture among circles on tray. Bake pavlovas for about 45 mins or until crisp and dry. Cool in oven with door ajar.
Just before serving, beat cream and 1 tbsp sugar in small bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form. Top pavlovas with cream and strawberries and coarsely grated chocolate.

title: kashmiri meatballs with spinach raita
directions: To make the meatballs, heat oil in a small frying pan over medium heat. Cook onion, garlic, ginger and curry paste, stirring, for 5 mins, or until onion is soft. Transfer to a large bowl and mix in cilantro, raisins, cashews and ground beef. Cover and chill for 15 mins.

Roll level tablespoons of mixture into balls then thread onto 12 skewers. Oil a large nonstick frying pan and place over medium-high heat. Working in batches, cook skewers until browned all over and cooked through.

Meanwhile, to make the spinach raita, boil, steam or microwave spinach until just wilted. Drain then squeeze out excess liquid. Transfer to a food processor and process spinach with remaining ingredients until smooth. Serve with meatballs.

title: ground beef and onion pot pie with cheese crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Combine flour, baking powder, 4 tbsp butter, milk, 1/2 tsp salt and cheese then knead with your hands. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 15-20 mins.

Meanwhile, heat 2 tbsp butter in a large frying pan and saute onions for 2-3 mins, stirring. Add ground beef and saute for 3-4 mins. Add cabbage and continue to cook for 1-2 mins. Add Worcestershire sauce and season. Transfer to a baking dish and set aside.
Roll out dough on a lightly floured work surface to 2/3 inch thick. Cut out 2 inch discs and cover ground beef mixture. Bake for 15 mins. Remove from oven and serve.

title: pistachio dacquoise with chocolate cream
directions: For the dacquoise, preheat oven to 300°F. Trace 2 - 7 inch circles onto 2 pieces of parchment paper and place on baking sheets. Mix ground nuts with 1/3 cup powdered sugar. Beat egg whites until stiff then gradually beat in remaining powdered sugar. Fold in ground pistachio mixture and transfer to a piping bag fitted with a medium plain tip. Starting from the outer edge, pipe the mixture into a spiral, filling the circle. Repeat with remaining circle. Bake for 15-20 mins or until just firm. Set aside to cool.

For the chocolate cream, place chocolate in a bowl. Heat cream until hot but not boiling and pour over chocolate. Let melt, stirring frequently. Add butter and set aside to cool. Once cool, whisk until thickened. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a large plain tip. Place 1 dacquoise on a plate and pipe chocolate cream on top. Add second dacquoise. Sprinkle remaining pistachios and sliced almonds over top. Serve dusted with powdered sugar.

title: cream of pea soup
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan over medium-low heat, add the onions and cook for 6-8 mins until soft but not browned. Add the potatoes and 1 1/2 cups peas, stir well and add the broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 15 mins until the potatoes are soft.

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and cook for 5-6 mins until golden. Stir in the ham and remaining peas and cook for 2-3 mins. Remove from the heat and set aside.

Puree the soup in a blender or food processor until smooth. Return the puree to the saucepan, stir in the cream and season with salt and pepper. Gently warm through. Divide the soup among bowls, spoon over the mushroom mixture and serve hot.

title: chicken osso buco
directions: Toss chicken in flour, shaking off excess. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Working in batches, cook chicken until browned all over.

Add remaining oil to pan. Cook leek and garlic, stirring, until leek is soft. Add reserved flour and tomato paste. Cook, stirring, for 1 min. Stir in stock, wine and tomatoes. Bring to a boil then return chicken to pan. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour 15 mins. Add celery and carrots. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 mins, or until vegetables are soft.
Meanwhile, combine lemon zest, parsley and garlic in a small bowl. Sprinkle over chicken to serve.

title: warm pasta salad with chicken and peppers
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling salted water according to the package instructions. Drain and keep warm.
Heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan and brown the chicken. Add the whole peppers and season with salt and black pepper. Cook over medium heat for 5 mins.
To make the dressing, mix the vinegar, pesto and 4 tbsp oil. Toss with the pasta. Arrange the pasta, chicken and peppers on plates and garnish with olives and basil.

title: baked fish with chermoula
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking tray with foil.
In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup cilantro, olive oil, spices and 1/2 of the lemon zest. Pour over fish in a shallow baking dish and set aside to marinate for 10 mins.
Arrange fish on prepared tray. Bake for 5-7 mins, until cooked through.

Meanwhile, place couscous and remaining lemon zest in a bowl. Add lemon juice and 1/2 cup boiling water. Cover with plastic wrap and let stand for 5 mins. Fluff with a fork then fold in remaining cilantro. Season to taste.
Serve couscous with fish and beans.

title: salmon sushi
directions: For the sushi rice, combine rice, 2 cups water and sake. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 mins, until all liquid is absorbed. Set aside, covered, for 15 mins. Meanwhile, combine mirin, sugar and 1 tsp salt. Mix with rice then spread out over a large, shallow baking dish. Let cool.

Line a 7x11 inch rimmed baking tray with plastic wrap. Thinly slice salmon 1/8 inch thick. Arrange in prepared pan, overlapping slices slightly. Top with nori then sushi rice. Cover with plastic wrap. Cut a piece of cardboard into a 7x11 inch rectangle then place over rice. Weigh down with cans and chill for 3 hours.
Remove sushi from tray and cut into squares. Serve with wasabi and soy sauce.

title: vodka martini
directions: Place the olive and a dash of dry vermouth into a chilled martini glass and swirl the vermouth in the glass to coat.
Place the ice cubes and vodka in cocktail shaker and shake vigorously. Strain into the glass, add the olive and serve.

title: savory buckwheat pancakes
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into large bowl. Gradually whisk in the combined eggs and buttermilk until smooth. Stir in the butter, grated vegetables and corn.

Heat a lightly oiled skillet on medium heat. Pour in 1/3 cup batter and cook until bubbles appear on the surface. Turn the pancake and cook until browned lightly. Repeat with remaining batter to make a total of 10 pancakes.
Serve pancakes topped with spreadable cream cheese and additional corn kernels, if desired.

title: one-pot chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Mix the cornstarch and dried thyme in a bowl and coat the chicken thighs. Heat half of the olive oil and the butter in a large Dutch oven and brown the chicken, skin down, for 3-4 mins. Turn and cook for another 2-3 mins or until the chicken is golden. Set chicken aside.

Return the dish to the heat, add the remaining olive oil and saute the onion and garlic for 4-5 mins until softened, then add the spring greens and cook for 3-4 mins. Stir in the stock and potatoes, season to taste and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 5 mins, then add the broccoli, scallions and chicken, skin side up. Bake, uncovered, for 15-20 mins until the potatoes are tender and the chicken is cooked through.

Meanwhile, combine the basil, tarragon and pine nuts in a food processor, adding the extra virgin olive oil slowly to make a pesto. Add pesto to the chicken, and serve garnished with basil and tarragon.

title: blueberry cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. In a bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder and sugar. In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg, milk and oil. Add the flour mixture then stir in the frozen blueberries. Divide mixture between 6 small, greased, oven-proof glasses with airtight seal-able lids, about 1 1/4 cup capacity. Bake in the center of the oven for about 35 minutes, until a knife inserted comes out clean.

Place the lids in boiling water for 2 minutes to sterilize, then drain on a towel. Remove the cakes from the oven and seal immediately with the sterilized lids. The cakes should keep, unopened, for about 4 weeks.

title: tomato and bean soup with cheese croutons
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan on high heat. Saute the onion and garlic for 1-2 mins, until tender. Stir in the stock and tomato and simmer for 5 mins. Add the beans and simmer for a further 4-5 mins until slightly thickened. Season to taste.

Meanwhile, preheat the broiler. Arrange the bread on a foil-lined baking pan. Broil for 1-2 mins, until golden. Turn the slices over then sprinkle with cheese. Broil for 1-2 mins, until the cheese melts.
Sprinkle the soup with chives or parsley and serve with cheese croutons.

title: curried beef and lentils
directions: Cook split peas in boiling water until just tender. Drain.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook onion, tomato and curry powder, stirring, until onion softens. Add split peas, bolognese sauce and raisins. Bring to a boil.
Serve curried beef with toast. Top with yogurt.

title: chicken and camembert parcels
directions: Preheat oven 400°F. Lightly grease a baking tray.

Spread mustard over chicken. Top with Camembert and basil. Wrap 1 slice of prosciutto around each piece of chicken. Lay 2 sheets of filo dough on a clean work surface. Lightly coat with oil or butter then fold in half. Top with 1 piece of chicken and wrap up into a parcel. Place on prepared tray and lightly with oil. Repeat with remaining filo and chicken. Sprinkle parcels with sesame seeds and bake for 20-25 mins, until golden brown and crispy.
Serve with baby spinach.

title: warm vegetable salad
directions: For the vinaigrette, whisk 1/4 cup of the oil and vinegar in a small bowl. Season to taste.

Heat remaining 2 tsp oil in a large skillet on high heat. Saute onion, garlic and chili pepper for 1-2 mins, until fragrant. Add peppers, zucchini, eggplant and mushrooms. Cook, stirring, for 3-5 mins, until tender.
Add the chickpeas and 1/2 the vinaigrette to vegetable mixture. Toss gently to combine. Remove from heat.
Place spinach in a large bowl. Drizzle with remaining vinaigrette and toss. Top with warm vegetable mixture and sprinkle with pine nuts.

title: lamb kebabs with mint yogurt sauce
directions: For the yogurt sauce, blend the garlic, sugar, lemon juice, mint and half the yogurt in a blender until smooth. Stir in the remaining yogurt and season to taste.
For the kebabs, mix the spices with the olive oil in a bowl, then add the lamb, mixing to coat thoroughly. Cover and leave to marinate 1 hour. Soak 12 wooden skewers in water 1 hour.
For the salad, combine the tomatoes, cucumbers, onion and parsley in a bowl. Toss with the olive oil and lemon juice and season to taste with sea salt and pepper.

Thread lamb cubes tightly onto the wooden skewers, about 5 pieces per skewer. Heat a barbecue or griddle pan to hot and cook skewers 5 mins, or until cooked as desired, turning. Serve with the yogurt sauce, salad and flatbread.

title: rhubarb and cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large heavy-bottomed saucepan over low heat. Cook, stirring, for 2-3 mins, or until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Boil for 10 mins then reduce heat and simmer for 40-45 mins, or until liquid reduces and mixture thickens.

title: chicken and meatball soup
directions: In a large pot combine the chicken, onion wedges, carrots, leek, salt, peppercorns, bay leaves, and 2 quarts water and bring to a boil. Simmer over a low-medium heat for 1 hour. Remove the chicken with a slotted spoon and use elsewhere. Drain the stock through a strainer. Discard the solids.

Heat 4 tbsp oil in a saucepan and saute the diced onions until softened. Add the flour and saute for 2 mins. Gradually add the stock and the cream, stirring constantly. Season with salt and black pepper and simmer over a low heat for 10 mins, stirring occasionally.

To make the meatballs, mix the ground beef, mint, breadcrumbs and egg. Season with salt and black pepper. Form into small balls. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan and cook the meatballs for 5 mins, turning, until browned. Drain on a paper towel.
For the croutons, heat 3 tbsp oil in a separate pan and saute the garlic and pitta bread until browned all over. Stir in the parsley and remove from the heat.
Stir the lemon juice and zest into the soup and season to taste. Ladle into bowls and top with the meatballs and pita croutons.

title: mini irish soda breads
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.

Whisk together flour, baking soda, salt, sugar and currants. Stir in buttermilk until just combined. Transfer to a floured work surface and knead until combined. Shape into 12 balls. Cut an "X" in the top of each bun. Brush tops with butter then bake for 12-15 mins, or until golden brown.

title: herb and garlic sausage
directions: Preheat broil. Coil each length of sausages into a long, tight spiral. Pierce 2 large metal skewers at right angles through each sausage coil to secure.

In a small bowl, combine lemon zest, lemon juice and remaining ingredients. Sprinkle 1/2 over sausage then broil until browned on top. Flip over and sprinkle with remaining lemon mixture and broil until browned and cooked through.

title: sweet chili fish parcels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 4 large pieces of foil with parchment paper. Distribute pak choy, carrot, pepper and fish between each piece of paper. Combine chili sauce, oyster sauce and sesame oil then drizzle over fish. Top with ginger then fold each into a parcel. Place, seam-side down, on a baking tray and bake for 20-25 mins or until fish is cooked through.

Meanwhile, place rice in a medium saucepan. Rinse under cold water until water runs clear then drain. Add coconut milk and 1 2/3 cups water, cover and bring to a boil. Cook for 10-12 mins or until liquid is almost absorbed. Remove from heat and let stand 5 mins. Fluff rice with a fork to separate grains. Remove fish from parcels and serve with rice. Garnish with fresh cilantro.

title: lentil shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Boil, steam or microwave potatoes until tender. Drain then mash with milk and spring onions until smooth.
Meanwhile, cook lentils in boiling water until just tender. Rinse under water then drain.

Heat oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion, pepper, zucchini, eggplant and garlic, stirring, until softened. Add tomatoes and lentils. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 mins, or until thickened. Season to taste.
Spoon into a baking dish and top with mashed potatoes. Bake for 30 mins, or until top is lightly browned.

title: roast stuffed turkey with cranberry sauce and gravy
directions: Melt the butter in a large skillet on medium heat. Cook the onions for 5 mins or until softened. Add the chicken livers and cook for a further 5 mins. Spoon into a large bowl and set aside to cool. Add the breadcrumbs, parsley, sage and sausage meat and mix thoroughly. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.

Preheat the oven to 350°F. Spoon the stuffing into the neck end of the turkey and smooth down the flap of skin to enclose the stuffing. Weigh the stuffed turkey and calculate the cooking time allowing 20 mins per pound. Place the turkey in a large roasting pan. Brush all over with oil. Cover with foil.

Roast for the calculated cooking time, basting occasionally. Remove the foil for the last 40 mins of cooking time. To check the turkey is cooked through, pierce the thickest part of the thigh with a skewer. The juices that run out should be clear, with no sign of pink. Transfer turkey a warm platter. Let stand, loosely covered with foil, for 30 mins.

For the cranberry sauce, place the sugar and 3/4 cup water in a small saucepan on medium-high heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 mins. Add the cranberries and simmer gently for a further 10 mins.

For the the gravy, pour off any excess fat from the roasting pan. Heat the cooking juices in the pan on medium heat. Whisk in the flour and cook, stirring for 1-2 mins. Gradually pour in the stock and bring to a boil, stirring. Reduce the heat to low; stir in the cream. Simmer for 5 mins. Season to taste.
Serve the turkey with the cranberry sauce and gravy with creamy mashed potatoes and seasonal cooked vegetables of your choice.

title: chocolate thunder brownie ice cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line an 8 inch square baking pan with foil then coat with oil.

Make brownie mix according to package instructions, adding toffee bits, toasted pecans and vanilla. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 40 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool completely then chill for 2 hours, or until cold.
Place heavy cream in a saucepan. Bring just to a boil then remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips. Let cool for 5 mins then whisk until smooth.

Remove chilled brownie from pan and transfer to a serving platter. Arrange 9 scoops of frozen yogurt over brownie then top each with a little chocolate sauce. Top with whipped cream, strawberries, chocolate shavings and remaining chopped pecans and toffee bits.

title: warm german potato salad
directions: Boil, steam or microwave potatoes until tender, drain.
Meanwhile, make the dressing by combining ingredients in a screw-top jar and shaking well.

Cook bacon in a heated medium frying pan, over medium heat, stirring, for 5 mins or until crisp. Drain on paper towels. Cook onion in same pan, stirring, for 5 mins, until softened. Add mustard seeds, cook, stirring, for 1 min.
Combine potatoes, bacon, onion mixture, parsley and dressing in a large bowl. Season to taste.

title: celery root and cheddar soup
directions: Heat the butter and oil in a large saucepan with a well fitting lid. Add the onion and cook until soft. Add the celery root and potato to the pan and stir well. Cook covered over medium low heat for 10 mins, shaking the pan from time to time. Add the apple and the chicken stock, bring to a boil and simmer uncovered for 15 mins. Add the crumbled cheese and stir. Serve in bowls sprinkled with the rest of the cheese.

title: basic vanilla custard
directions: Heat the milk, cream, vanilla pod and seeds in a saucepan over medium heat until just simmering. Remove from heat and cool 10 mins, to infuse. Whisk together egg yolks and sugar in a bowl until pale and creamy, then gradually whisk into warm milk mixture. Return to the pan and stir over low heat 8-10 mins, until mixture coats the back of a wooden spoon. Strain through a fine sieve and discard the vanilla bean. Serve warm or refrigerate, covered, and serve cold.

title: herby scrambled egg breakfast wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Place tomatoes, cut-side up, on prepared tray. Season. Bake for 20 mins.

Whisk together eggs, milk and herbs. Season. Melt butter in a small saucepan over low heat. Add egg mixture and heat gently, stirring, for 3-5 mins, until just set. Distribute between tortillas along with tomatoes. Roll up and serve.

title: chocolate orange and date squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line a 12 x 8-inch baking pan with parchment paper, extending the paper over long sides for handles.
Beat butter and brown sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in sifted flours, dates, orange juice, chocolate chips, walnuts and orange peel, until combined. Spoon into prepared pan, smoothing top.
Bake for 35-40 mins, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 mins. Remove from pan; completely on wire rack.

For the cream cheese icing, beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and orange peel in a medium bowl with electric mixer until smooth. Spread over cooled dessert and sprinkle with toasted coconut. Cut into squares.

title: mushroom and sesame stuffed tofu
directions: Cut tofu into 4 equal squares. Using a small knife, cut a small pocket in the top of each square. Using a small spoon, scoop out tofu curd leaving a 1/3-inch shell; reserve tofu curd.

Heat oil in a large skillet over moderately high heat. Add celery and onion; saute for 2 minutes or until soft. Add garlic; saute for 30 seconds or until fragrant. Add mushroom; saute for 5 minutes or until tender. Add reserved tofu curd and sesame seeds; saute for 1-2 minutes or until heated. Season. Remove from heat.
Divide mushroom mixture among tofu shells. Place tofu in a 9-inch (base measurement) round, shallow heatproof dish. Combine stock and soy sauce in a small bowl. Pour into base of dish.

Place dish in a large steaming basket set over a large saucepan, or wok, of simmering water. Cover basket with foil; steam for 7 minutes or until tofu is heated. Remove saucepan from heat. Carefully remove dish from basket. Top tofu with extra onion and chili. Serve with rice and Asian greens.

title: piri piri chicken sandwich
directions: In a bowl, combine ground chicken, bread crumbs, piri piri sauce, onions and garlic. Season. Shape into 4 patties. Chill.

Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook patties for 4-5 mins per side, until golden and cooked through. Place a slice of cheese on each patty. Cover pan with lid and set aside for 1-2 mins, until cheese melts.
Meanwhile, to make the spicy mayonnaise, whisk together mayonnaise, piri piri sauce and lemon juice. Season.
Fill each roll with lettuce, avocado and tomato. Top with patties. Serve with spicy mayonnaise.

title: prosciutto and fig mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Lightly grease 10 holes of two 6-hole Texas muffin pans. Cut 20 strips of parchment paper 1 x 5 inches long. Line each recess with 2 strips, crossing at the base.
Process crackers in a food processor until finely crushed. Add butter, and pulse to combine. Divide mixture between recesses and press firmly into base. Chill.

To make the filling: Heat a non-stick frying pan on medium. Add chopped prosciutto and cook for 2 mins. Add onion and garlic and cook for 2-3 mins, until onion is tender and prosciutto is crisp. In a large bowl, beat ricotta and cream cheese until smooth. Add eggs and yolks one at a time and beat until combined. Mix in prosciutto mixture and Parmesan.
Divide filling among prepared muffin pans. Bake for 25-30 mins, until just firm. Set aside until cooled slightly, then remove from pan.
Preheat broiler on high. Place prosciutto strips on a foil-lined baking sheet and broil for 1-2 mins each side, until crisp. Serve cheesecakes topped with crisp prosciutto and figs.

title: tahini dip
directions: Combine the tahini and lemon juice in a medium bowl. Add 1/3 cup water; stir until smooth. Season to taste with sea salt and freshly ground white pepper.
Place the dip in a small serving bowl. Drizzle with the olive oil and sprinkle with paprika. Serve with flatbread and vegetables.

title: light chocolate cake
directions: For the icing, sift together powdered sugar and cocoa powder. Add coffee and mix until smooth and spreadable. Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a deep, 8 inch round cake pan with oil. Line base with parchment paper.

Cream sugar and spread together until smooth and creamy. Add egg, beating until combined. Sift together flour and cocoa powder. Alternately add flour mixture with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Combine 1/4 cup boiling water and baking soda. Fold into batter. Transfer to prepared pan. Bake for 35-40 mins, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Spread icing over cooled cake.

title: individual creamed corn and bacon soufflés
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Lightly grease 4 x 1-cup ramekins with butter. Dust with Parmesan.

Melt butter in medium frying pan on high. Saute bacon and onion 3-4 mins, until golden. Add flour and cook, stirring, 1 min. Transfer to a bowl. Cool slightly. In a small bowl, whisk corn and egg yolks together. Stir in bacon mixture. In a medium bowl, using an electric mixer, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Lightly fold into corn and bacon mixture. Spoon into ramekins. Run a finger around the inside of each to create a rim. Place on a baking sheet and bake 15-20 mins, until puffed and golden. Serve hot with baby spinach leaves.

title: mini cinnamon doughnuts with jam and cream
directions: Combine milk, 1 tbsp sugar and yeast in a small bowl. Let stand for 5-10 mins until frothy.
Meanwhile, sift flour and salt into a large bowl. Stir in remaining 1 tbsp sugar. Stir in butter mixture. Mix to a soft, sticky dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead for about 10 mins until smooth. Place into a large, oiled bowl. Cover with a tea towel or plastic wrap. Let stand about 45 mins or until doubled in size.

Punch down dough to remove air. Knead until smooth. Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness. Using a 1 3/4-inch round cookie cutter, cut into rounds. Place the doughnuts on lightly greased baking pans. Cover loosely with plastic wrap. Let stand about 20 mins or until doubled in size.
Heat the oil in a large saucepan on medium heat. Deep-fry doughnuts, 3 or 4 at a time, turning, for 3-5 mins until golden and cooked through. Drain on paper towels.

Mix remaining 1 cup sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl. Toss warm doughnuts in cinnamon sugar. Serve with jam and cream. (For doughnut sandwiches, cut each doughnut in half, spread one side with jam and cream, then top with remaining half.)

title: nutella brownie muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease a 12-cup muffin pan.

Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl. Whisk together butter, Nutella, egg, milk and sour cream. Mix into dry ingredients until just combined then fold in chocolate chips and pistachios. Distribute between muffin recesses and bake for 20 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Dust with extra cocoa powder to serve.

title: grilled vegetable salad
directions: Heat a grill pan on high heat or preheat the grill to medium-high.
Spray the pepper, sweet potato and eggplant lightly with no stick cooking spray. Grill for 5-10 mins, turning, until golden and tender.
Meanwhile, for the balsamic dressing, whisk all ingredients in a small bowl. Season to taste.
Combine the grilled vegetables, chickpeas, spinach, basil leaves and mozzarella cheese in a large bowl. Drizzle with dressing just before serving.

title: warm pasta provençale salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente then drain.
Meanwhile, oil a large frying pan and place over high heat. Cook lamb chops for 3 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from pan, cover and let rest for 5 mins. Slice thickly.
Transfer pasta and lamb to a large bowl along with remaining ingredients and toss gently to combine. Season to taste. Serve warm.

title: blueberry, lime and passionfruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease an 8x12 inch rimmed baking pan. Line base and long sides with parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches over sides.

Whip egg whites until frothy. Stir in ground almonds, powdered sugar, flour, coconut, butter and lime zest. Transfer to prepared pan. Sprinkle with blueberries and drizzle with passionfruit pulp. Bake for 1 hour 15 mins. Let cool in pan for 10 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Cut into rectangles and dust with powdered sugar to serve.

title: exotic mini pizzas
directions: Dissolve the yeast with 1/2 cup warm water. Mix the flour, 1 tsp salt and 1 tsp sugar in a large bowl, add the yeast mixture and oil and knead into a smooth dough. Cover and keep in a warm place for about 10 mins. Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and knead again for 2-3 mins to de-gas. Divide the dough into 8 pieces, roll into 4 inch discs and transfer to a lined baking tray.

Preheat oven to 400°F. On each mini pizza, place a slice of pineapple, some diced turkey, cheese and cayenne. Cover and set aside for 10 mins then bake for 10 mins. Sprinkle with the coconut then return to the oven for another 5 mins. Serve garnished with mint.

title: scallops with saffron cream sauce and prosciutto
directions: Preheat broiler to high. Line an oven tray with baking paper.
Place prosciutto on tray. Broil for 3-4 minutes, until crisp. Allow to cool and crumble into small pieces. Set aside.

In a small saucepan, combine wine, lemon juice and shallot. Bring to a boil on medium. Boil 3-4 minutes, until reduced by two-thirds. Reduce heat to low. Stir in cream and saffron. Simmer for 2-3 minutes.
Strain sauce and return to a clean saucepan. Heat on medium while adding butter in batches and whisking in until smooth. Season to taste and keep warm.

Remove scallops and clean shells. Melt extra butter in large frying pan on medium. Sear scallops for 30-60 seconds each side, until lightly browned and cooked through. Return to shells and spoon sauce over. Sprinkle with prosciutto and chives. Serve straight away with lime wedges.

title: fettuccine with ratatouille and ricotta cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F. Combine eggplant, zucchini, pepper and onions in a large roasting pan. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Bake for 15 mins or until golden brown and tender.
Add tomatoes, garlic, chili and vinegar to vegetables and mix well. Bake for 10 mins or until cooked.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water for 10-12 mins or until tender. Drain and reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid.
Stir reserved cooking liquid into the ratatouille. Add pasta and basil to ratatouille and mix to combine. Spoon into shallow serving bowls. Serve topped with ricotta and extra basil leaves.

title: asparagus and gruyère tart
directions: In a food processor, combine flour, butter, cheese and paprika. Pulse until crumbly. Add egg yolk and 2 tsp ice water. Pulse until mixture just comes together. Transfer to a lightly floured work surface and knead until smooth. Wrap in plastic wrap then chill for 30 mins.
Roll pastry out until 1/8 inch-thick then use to line a 13x4 inch tart pan, trimming edges. Freeze for 30 mins.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Line tart shell with parchment paper and fill with pie weights. Place on a baking tray and blind bake for 15 mins. Remove paper and weights and bake for another 10 mins. Let cool.

Meanwhile, for the filling, heat butter in a large saucepan over low heat. Cook onion for 10 mins, or until very soft. Spread over base of tart shell. Arrange asparagus on top then sprinkle with cheese. Whisk eggs, flour and cream together and season to taste. Pour over asparagus.
Increase heat to 400°F. Bake tart for 20 mins, or until golden brown and just set in the center.

title: chicken schnitzel with potato salad
directions: Season the chicken to taste with salt and pepper and sprinkle it with half the lemon juice. Mix together the mustard, egg yolks, lemon zest, cream, and a pinch of sugar. Coat the chicken, first with flour, then with the egg yolk mixture and let marinate for 2-3 hours.

Meanwhile, cook the potatoes in boiling water for about 20 minutes. When they're done, drain, rinse, peel, and slice them. Combine the the stock, vinegar, 2 tbsp of oil, 1 tbsp of sugar, and the onion in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Stir in the herbs, season to taste, and pour the mixture over the potatoes. Cover and set aside.
Melt the butter, cook until it's light brown, and remove it from the heat. Stir in the remaining lemon juice, a pinch of salt, and 1 tbsp of sugar. Pour it over the lettuce and serve it in bowls.
Heat 3 tbsp of oil in a pan. Cook the chicken schnitzel for 3-5 minutes on each side.
Serve schnitzel with the potato salad, garnished with parsley and lemon slices.

title: vegetable tortilla wraps with hummus and ricotta celery sticks
directions: Place tortillas on a flat work surface. Spread hummus over top. Add mixed greens, carrot, pepper and tomatoes. Roll up tightly to enclose filling. Halve.
In a small bowl, mix ricotta with chives. Spread down the center of each piece of celery. Serve with tortilla wraps.

title: coconut fish with pineapple raita
directions: In a food processor, combine fish, curry paste, cilantro, ginger, egg white and garlic. Pulse until combined. Season then transfer to a large bowl and fold in green beans. Chill until firm.
Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Shape heaped tablespoonfuls of mixture into fish fingers. Coat in coconut then place on prepared tray and chill for 20 mins.
Meanwhile, for the raita, combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Season to taste. Chill until required.
Heat oil in a deep frying pan over high heat. Fry fish fingers, in batches, for 1-2 mins per side, until golden brown and cooked through. Drain on paper towels. Serve with raita and lime wedges.

title: chicken macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat broiler.

Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and cook for 1 min. Slowly whisk in milk. Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens. Reduce heat and simmer for 3 mins. Combine cheese then add 1/2 to sauce. Stir until melted and combined. Toss with macaroni, chicken and corn. Season. Transfer to a large baking dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Broil for 4-5 mins, until cheese is melted and golden brown.
Serve with mixed greens.
